The programs is coming from https://github.com/kevinkm/get_rm_command, if you have broadlink rm/rm2/rm pro,
and you want to build it at homeassistant you may need this program.


~$ wget https://github.com/kevinkm/get_rm_command/blob/master/rm2.py
~$ wget https://github.com/kevinkm/get_rm_command/blob/master/configuration.yaml
~$ mv -f configuration.yaml your homeassistant directory
~$ python3 rm2.py

visit youtube for HOWTO:hht